# Phase & Spec Discipline

> Phase tracker (source of truth): `openspec/config.yaml`
> Phase specs: `openspec/specs/` | SDD workflow: `docs/agentic-os.md`

## Before Starting Any Phase Work
1. Read current state from `openspec/config.yaml` — do not assume phase from memory
2. Read the relevant spec in `openspec/specs/`
3. Declare scope explicitly and get human approval for any destructive step
4. Create a git checkpoint commit before any apply batch

## Spec Format
- Use Given/When/Then for scenarios
- Use RFC 2119 keywords: MUST, SHALL, SHOULD, MAY
- Every spec includes a rollback plan for risky changes

## Task Granularity
- Tasks small enough to complete in one session
- Hierarchical numbering: 1.1, 1.2, etc.
- Order: infrastructure → implementation → testing

